HEADWORD: Haüynite
<hw>Ha"⟦uum⟧y*nite</hw> <pr>(⟦aum⟧"w⟦esl⟧*n⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[From the French mineralogist <etsep>Ha⟦uum⟧y</etsep>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A blue isometric mineral, characteristic of some
volcanic rocks. It is a silicate of alumina, lime, and soda, with
sulphate of lime.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Havana</ent>⟦br⟧
